Bubble Sort 
Bubble Sort is a comparision based sorting algorithm that compares the next and previous values to sort their relative positions 
till the entire stack has been sorted in ascending/descending order.

The logic of the algorith,:-
1. Compare adjacent values
2.Swap if one is greater/smaller than the other (BASED ON ASCENDING OR DESCENDING NATURE OF STACK)
3.Continues till it reaches the end of file 
4. Repeats for each pass till the entire stack is sorted

Example: ascending
[3,5,2,7] (Compared 3 and 5 no swap)

first pass:
[3,2,5,7] (Compared 5 and 2 Swap found and swapped)

second pass:
[2,3,5,7] (Compared 5 and 7 and 3 and 2 found swap for 3 and 2 didnt find one for 5 and 7 so swapped 3 and 2)

third pass:
no swaps found so sorted

What makes your code efficient?

1.Make use of swap flags. This helps reduce excess looping and your code going through each value and check each value
A boolean Flag named swap tracks where swap occured in a pass. If no swaps occur the stack is already sorted therefore
the bubble sort program outputs result without going through the entire stack.

2.Reduced Comparisions
After every pass, one value is set to be in the maximum position which is true. Therefore after each pass
reduce the number of total values and exclude the already sorted value.
This makes the inner loop shorted each time making ur code quicker and more efficient.



